    "about": {
        "title": "About",
        "items": [
            {
                "order": 10,
                "text": "Author: Matthew Eater",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 20,
                "text": "I made this one day when I was working on a floor leveling project and thought it would be nice to have a calculator to help me out.",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 30,
                "text": "The basic principal is that you use a laser level to determine the relative heights of the high and low spots in the floor, measure the distances between those points, and then input that data into this calculator to get the thickness of the leveling compound to use at each point.",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 40,
                "text": "Eventually I want to add a feature that calculates the volume of compound required, but I think this will require either a more complex system for inputting points via a coordinate system, or it will require the user to only take measures that create triangles so that the topology of the floor can be calculated trigonomically.",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 50,
                "text": "This is a work in progress, and I welcome any feedback or suggestions for improvement.",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 60,
                "text": "Thanks for using my calculator!",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 70,
                "text": "...",
                "action": "none"
            },
            {
                "order": 80,
                "text": "This isn't a real menu, so just hit enter to return to the main menu.",
                "action": "back_to_main_menu"
            }
        ]
    },
